-- Etisalat Aims to Have 7 Million Nigerian Subscribers by Year End, CEO Says
-- B y   N i c k y   S m i t h
-- 2010-11-10T13:38:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-10/etisalat-aims-to-have-7-million-nigerian-subscribers-by-year-end-ceo-says.html
Emirates Telecommunications Corp.’s
Nigerian unit aims to have 7 million customers by the end of
this year after crossing the 6 million mark last week, Steven
Evans, the chief executive officer of the unit, said.  Etisalat has been offering services in Africa’s most
populous country for the past two years, Evans said in a speech
at the AfricaCom conference in Cape Town today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nicky Smith in Johannesburg at 
